b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe15033.htm)  [Next](sbe15035.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B002DEMBWG/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_The Upanishads, Part 2 (SBE15)_ , by Max Muller, [1879], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 54\n\n## SECOND VALL\xc3\x8e,\n\n## OR, THE CHAPTER ON \xc3\x82NANDA (BLISS).\n\nHari _h_ , Om! May it (the Brahman) protect us both (teacher and pupil)! May\nit enjoy us both! May we acquire strength together! May our knowledge become\nbright! May we never quarrel! Peace! peace! peace 1!\n\n### FIRST ANUV\xc3\x82KA.\n\nHe who knows the Brahman attains the highest (Brahman). On this the following\nverse is recorded:\n\n'He who knows Brahman, which is (i.e. cause, not effect), which is conscious,\nwhich is without end, as hidden in the depth (of the heart), in the highest\nether, he enjoys all blessings, at one with the omniscient Brahman.'\n\nFrom that Self 2 (Brahman) sprang ether (aka _s_ a, that through which we\nhear); from ether air (that through which we hear and feel); from air fire\n(that through which we hear, feel, and see); from fire water (that through\nwhich we hear, feel, see, and taste); from water earth (that through which we\nhear, feel, see, taste, and smell). From earth herbs, from herbs food, from\nfood seed, from seed man. Man thus consists of the essence of food. This is\nhis head,\n\np. 55\n\nthis his right arm, this his left arm, this his trunk (\xc3\x82tman), this the seat\n(the support) [1](sbe15035.htm#fn_214).\n\nOn this there is also the following _S_ loka:\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[54:1](sbe15034.htm#fr_212) Not counted here as an Anuvaka. The other Anuvakas\nare divided into a number of small sentences.\n\n[54:2](sbe15034.htm#fr_213) Compare with this s _ri_ sh _t_ ikrama, _Kh_ and.\nUp. VI, 2; Ait. \xc3\x82r. II, 4, 1.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: II, 2](sbe15035.htm)\n\n"